## Meeting Practices That Respect Deep Work

### The Meeting Audit and Reduction

<Callout type="warning" title="Ruthless Meeting Reduction">
Top distributed companies are ruthless about meeting reduction. Every meeting must justify its existence.
</Callout>

<Checklist title="Meeting Audit Questions">
- [ ] Could this be handled async?
- [ ] Is there a clear decision or output needed?
- [ ] Is everyone invited necessary?
- [ ] Is the time allocated appropriate?
- [ ] Is this recurring meeting still valuable?
</Checklist>

<Tabs>
<Tab label="Meeting Replacement Alternatives">
- **Status Updates:** → Async standup or shared doc
- **Brainstorming:** → Shared document + comment period
- **Decision Making:** → Async proposal + focused discussion call
- **Information Sharing:** → Documentation + FAQ section
- **1:1 Check-ins:** → Structured async weekly update
</Tab>
<Tab label="Meeting Efficiency Checklist">
- [ ] Agenda shared 24+ hours in advance
- [ ] Clear objectives and expected outcomes
- [ ] Only essential attendees invited
- [ ] Timebox enforced (start/end times)
- [ ] Note-taker assigned
- [ ] Follow-up items documented with owners
</Tab>
</Tabs>

<Accordion>
<AccordionItem title="GitLab&apos;s Meeting Guidelines">
- Default to async (documentation, issue tracking, async video)
- Record all meetings for those who can't attend
- Take notes in public doc (live during meeting)
- Meetings over 30 minutes must include breaks
- No agendas, no meeting
</AccordionItem>

<AccordionItem title="The Read-First Meeting">
- **Before:** Participants read proposal/document independently
- **During:** Discussion starts immediately (no presentation)
- **Benefit:** Respects time, leverages async thinking
</AccordionItem>

<AccordionItem title="The Silent Meeting">
- **Format:** First 10 minutes, everyone writes responses in shared doc
- **Then:** Group discusses responses
- **Benefit:** Extroverts don't dominate, introverts have space
</AccordionItem>

<AccordionItem title="The Problem-Solving Meeting (1 hour)">
1. **Context (5 min):** Problem statement
2. **Ideas (15 min):** Silent brainstorm in shared doc
3. **Cluster (5 min):** Group related ideas
4. **Vote (5 min):** Dot vote on most promising
5. **Discuss (15 min):** Deep dive on top 2-3 ideas
6. **Decide (5 min):** Next steps and owners
</AccordionItem>

<AccordionItem title="The 1:1 Meeting">
- **Focus:** Growth, coaching, relationship-building (not status updates)
- **Frequency:** Biweekly for 30-45 minutes
- **Format:**
  - Check-in (how are you?)
  - Wins and challenges
  - Growth and development
  - Feedback (give and receive)
  - Roadmap look-ahead
</AccordionItem>
</Accordion>

