## Building Trust Without Proximity

### The Trust Equation

**Trust = (Credibility + Reliability + Intimacy) / Self-Orientation**

**Increase Credibility:**
- Demonstrate competence through consistent output
- Share expertise generously in public channels
- Admit when you don't know (builds more trust than blustering)

**Increase Reliability:**
- Do what you say you'll do, when you say you'll do it
- Communicate early if you'll miss a deadline
- Follow up consistently

**Increase Intimacy:**
- Share appropriate personal context
- Be vulnerable about challenges
- Show up as a whole person, not just a work role

**Decrease Self-Orientation:**
- Default to generosity in interpreting messages
- Share credit generously
- Ask "how can I help?" more than "what do you need?"

### Recognition and Appreciation Rituals

Remote workers can feel invisible. Intentional recognition counteracts this.

**Daily Appreciation:**
- #shoutouts channel (public recognition)
- Direct message appreciation (more personal)
- Emoji reactions (quick acknowledgment)

**Weekly Appreciation:**
- Team retro includes "appreciations" section
- Kudos in team all-hands
- Peer-to-peer recognition program

**Appreciation Formula:** "Thank you for [specific action], which [specific impact]. I appreciate [quality the person demonstrated]."

<StepGuide title="Setting Up Recognition Systems">
<StepGuideStep title="Step 1: Choose Recognition Channels">
- Public: #shoutouts, team all-hands
- Private: Direct messages, peer-to-peer
- Formal: Recognition programs, awards
</StepGuideStep>
<StepGuideStep title="Step 2: Define Recognition Criteria">
- Specific behaviors to recognize
- Frequency (daily, weekly, monthly)
- Who can give/recognition
- Impact levels (individual, team, company)
</StepGuideStep>
<StepGuideStep title="Step 3: Implement Tools">
- Slack bots for automated recognition
- Recognition platforms like Bonusly
- Dedicated recognition channels
- Celebration rituals for milestones
</StepGuideStep>
<StepGuideStep title="Step 4: Train the Team">
- Practice giving specific recognition
- Share examples of good appreciation
- Make recognition part of regular rhythms
- Encourage peer-to-peer recognition
</StepGuideStep>
</StepGuide>

<Callout type="success" title="The Recognition ROI">
Teams with regular recognition see 31% lower voluntary turnover and 3x innovation rates. Recognition isn't just nice—it's strategic.
</Callout>

